body:
I added some conditional formatting to an excel sheet using ms-excel. And printed/ copied to new sheet in exceljs as follows:

```
if (oldSheet.conditionalFormattings) {
      oldSheet.conditionalFormattings.forEach((conditionalFormatting) => {
        console.log(conditionalFormatting);
        newSheet.addConditionalFormatting(conditionalFormatting);
      });
    }
```

this logs :

```
{
  ref: 'G2:G7',
  rules: [
    {
      type: 'containsText',
      operator: 'containsText',
      priority: 1,
      timePeriod: undefined,
      percent: undefined,
      bottom: undefined,
      rank: undefined,
      aboveAverage: undefined,
      formulae: [Array],
      style: [Object]
    }
  ]
}
```

and when I open new sheet it shows conditional format correctly.

Then I do few edits on excel sheet in ms excel then re run the excel sheet logs :
```

{
  rules: [
    {
      type: 'containsText',
      x14Id: '{FB6921CD-5991-484A-A817-95052B69C3E1}',
      priority: 1
    }
  ],
  ref: 'G2:G6'
}
```

new sheet is corrupted and ms excel asks to recover it. Once recovered no conditional formatting are there.

So, my problem is, How can I convert x14Id based rule to original rule format which supports copy and never corrupts the sheet.
